  "prompt": "How does UPS Next Day Air works?",
  "response": "UPS Next Day Air is a premium shipping service offered by UPS (United Parcel Service) that guarantees delivery by the next business day for domestic shipments within the United States. Here\u2019s how it works:\n\n### 1. **Service Options**:\n   - **Next Day Air Early**: Delivery by 8:00 AM the next business day.\n   - **Next Day Air**: Delivery by 10:30 AM the next business day.\n   - **Next Day Air Saver**: Delivery by the end of the next business day (typically by 3:00 PM).\n\n### 2. **Shipping Process**:\n   - **Pickup or Drop-off**: You can either schedule a pickup at your location or drop off your package at a UPS location or authorized shipping center.\n   - **Cut-off Times**: To ensure next-day delivery, shipments must be handed over to UPS by a specific cutoff time, which varies depending on the service option and location. This is usually in the afternoon or early evening (e.g., 7:00 PM for Next Day Air Saver).\n   - **Label and Documentation**: You\u2019ll need to create a shipping label, either online or at a UPS location, and include the necessary documentation.\n\n### 3. **Transportation**:\n   - Once picked up, UPS prioritizes Next Day Air shipments using its air and ground networks.\n   - Packages are typically flown to a regional hub and then sorted for final delivery.\n\n### 4. **Delivery**:\n   - UPS drivers deliver the package the next business day based on the chosen service level (early morning, morning, or end of day).\n   - Proof of delivery is available upon request.\n\n### 5. **Tracking and Notification**:\n   - You can track your shipment in real-time using the UPS tracking tool online or via the UPS app.\n   - UPS may also send notifications about the shipment\u2019s status and expected delivery time.\n\n### 6. **Additional Features**:\n   - **Guaranteed Delivery**: UPS offers a money-back guarantee if the package is not delivered by the promised time (though certain exclusions apply).\n   - **Signature Requirements**: You can specify if a signature is required upon delivery.\n\n### Key Considerations:\n   - **Holidays and Weekends**: Next Day Air is for business days only, so packages picked up on Friday will be delivered on Monday.\n   - **Cost**: This is one of UPS\u2019s most expensive services due to the expedited nature.\n   - **International**: For international shipping, UPS offers UPS Worldwide Express, which provides similar next-day delivery for select destinations.\n\nUPS Next Day Air is ideal for time-sensitive shipments where reliability and speed are critical.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
